original: At the first God made the heaven and the earth.
translation: Pada mulanya Allah menciptakan langit dan bumi.

original: And the earth was waste and without form; and it was dark on the face of the deep: and the Spirit of God was moving on the face of the waters.
translation: Dan bumi masih kosong dan tidak berbentuk, gelap gulita di atas permukaan samudra, dan Roh Allah melayang-layang di atas permukaan air.

original: And God said, Let there be light: and there was light.
translation: Dan Allah bersabda, "Jadilah terang," maka terang itu ada.

original: And God, looking on the light, saw that it was good: and God made a division between the light and the dark,
translation: Allah melihat cahaya itu, dan Dia tahu itu baik, lalu Allah membuat pemisahan antara cahaya dan kegelapan.

original: Naming the light, Day, and the dark, Night. And there was evening and there was morning, the first day.
translation: Menamai terang itu Hari, dan kegelapan, Malam. Lalu ada petang dan ada pagi, hari pertama.

original: And God said, Let there be a solid arch stretching over the waters, parting the waters from the waters.
translation: Allah berfirman, "Biarkanlah ada satu langit yang kuat membentang di atas air, memisahkan air dari air."

original: And God made the arch for a division between the waters which were under the arch and those which were over it: and it was so.
translation: Dan Allah membuat kenari untuk memisahkan air yang berada di bawah kenari dan air yang berada di atasnya: dan itu terjadi.

original: And God gave the arch the name of Heaven. And there was evening and there was morning, the second day.
translation: Dan Allah menamai langit itu Firman-Nya di langit, dan petang dan pagi hari, itulah hari kedua.

original: And God said, Let the waters under the heaven come together in one place, and let the dry land be seen: and it was so.
translation: Dan Allah berkata, "Biarkan air di bawah langit berkumpul di satu tempat, dan biarkan tanah kering kelihatan": dan itu terjadi.

original: And God gave the dry land the name of Earth; and the waters together in their place were named Seas: and God saw that it was good.
translation: Dan Allah menamai daratan kering itu bumi, dan kumpulan air itu dinamai laut: dan Allah melihat bahwa semuanya baik.

original: And God said, Let grass come up on the earth, and plants producing seed, and fruit-trees giving fruit, in which is their seed, after their sort: and it was so.
translation: Dan Allah berfirman, "Biarkan rumput tumbuh di bumi, dan tumbuh-tumbuhan yang menghasilkan biji, dan pohon-pohon buah yang menghasilkan buah, yang bijinya ada di dalamnya, menurut jenisnya": dan demikianlah terjadi.

original: And grass came up on the earth, and every plant producing seed of its sort, and every tree producing fruit, in which is its seed, of its sort: and God saw that it was good.
translation: Dan rumput tumbuh di bumi, dan setiap tanaman menghasilkan biji menurut jenisnya, dan setiap pohon menghasilkan buah, yang mengandung bijinya, menurut jenisnya: dan Allah melihat bahwa semuanya itu baik.

original: And there was evening and there was morning, the third day.
translation: Dan ada petang hari itu, dan ada pagi hari itu, hari ketiga.

original: And David in answer said to the priest, Certainly women have been kept from us; and as has been done before when I have gone out the arms of the young men were made holy, even though it was a common journey; how much more today will their arms be made holy.

original: Give praise to the Lord, O my soul; let everything in me give praise to his holy name.
translation: Puji Tuhan, hai jiwaku, biarkan segala yang ada di dalamku memuji nama-Nya yang kudus.

original: Give praise to the Lord, O my soul; let not all his blessings go from your memory.
translation: Puji Tuhan, hai jiwaku, jangan sampai semua berkat-Nya lenyap dari ingatanmu.

original: He has forgiveness for all your sins; he takes away all your diseases;
translation: Dia memiliki pengampunan untuk semua dosamu; Dia mengambil semua penyakitmu.

original: He keeps back your life from destruction, crowning you with mercy and grace.
translation: Dia menjaga hidupmu dari kehancuran, mengkaruniamu dengan kasih sayang dan anugerah.

original: He makes your mouth full of good things, so that your strength is made new again like the eagle's.
translation: Dia membuat mulutmu penuh dengan hal-hal yang baik, sehingga kekuatanmu diperbarui kembali seperti elang.

original: The Lord gives decisions in righteousness for all who are in trouble.
translation: Tuhan mengambil keputusan dengan adil bagi semua orang yang mengalami kesusahan.

original: He gave knowledge of his way to Moses, and made his acts clear to the children of Israel.
translation: Ia memberikan pengertian tentang jalan-Nya kepada Musa, dan membuat perbuatan-Nya nyata kepada anak-anak Israel.

original: The Lord is kind and full of pity, not quickly made angry, but ever ready to have mercy.
translation: Tuhan baik hati dan penuh belas kasihan, tidak mudah marah, tetapi selalu siap untuk menunjukkan belas kasihan.

original: His feeling will no longer be bitter; he will not keep his wrath for ever.
translation: Perasaannya tidak akan pahit lagi; dia tidak akan memendam kemarahannya selamanya.

original: He has not given us the punishment for our sins, or the reward of our wrongdoing.
translation: Dia tidak memberikan hukuman kepada kita karena dosa-dosa kita, atau balasan atas perbuatan salah kita.

original: For as the heaven is high over the earth, so great is his mercy to his worshippers.
translation: Seperti langit tinggi di atas bumi, begitulah besarnya kasih sayang-Nya kepada mereka yang menyembah-Nya.

original: As far as the east is from the west, so far has he put our sins from us.
translation: Sejauh timur dari barat, sejauh itu Dia telah menjauhkan dosa-dosa kita dari kita.

original: As a father has pity on his children, so the Lord has pity on his worshippers.
translation: Bagaikan seorang ayah yang menyayangi anak-anaknya, demikian Tuhan menyayangi orang-orang yang mengabdi kepada-Nya.
